  "doc_id": "17813",
  "text": "Our in vivo studies showed that CAS is effective against C. guilliermondii and C. parapsilosis. To our knowledge, this is the first study in which an echinocandin derivative is utilized in an experimental model of infection due to C. guilliermondii. As far as we know, all models have been done with C. albicans (including fluconazole-resistant isolates), Candida glabrata, Candida krusei, Candida tropicalis and C. parapsilosis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
